Coralogix DataPrime (tool: coralogix_execute_dataprime_query) queries logs/traces (sources: logs, spans).

Rules:
- Always set explicit time ranges: start_date/end_date
- Include `limit` on every query (start with limit 100 and adjust accordingly)
- Traces: use `source spans`
- Never query archive tier; only query frequent search data

Query Syntax - CRITICAL distinction between filter and lucene:
- `lucene 'text'` searches only the TEXT BODY of logs (message content)
- `filter $l.field == 'value'` filters by LABEL FIELDS (metadata like applicationname, subsystemname)
- Application name is ALWAYS a label: use `filter $l.applicationname == 'app-name'`
- To search for text AND filter by app: `source logs | filter $l.applicationname == 'my-app' | lucene 'error' | limit 100`
- To search text only: `source logs | lucene 'error text' | limit 100`

Common label fields: $l.applicationname, $l.subsystemname, $l.severity
To discover all available labels: run `source logs | limit 1` and examine the labels array in results

Example queries:
- Find ERROR logs for an app: `source logs | filter $l.applicationname == 'my-app' | filter $m.severity == 5 | limit 100`
- Search text across all apps: `source logs | lucene 'database timeout' | limit 100`
- Combine app filter with text search: `source logs | filter $l.applicationname == 'payment-api' | lucene 'ERR-' | limit 100`
